referred_to_by.value: Handwritten by O'Keeffe in pencil on verso: "Greetings for 1960 from my//poor house —//I go to N.Y.//tomorrow for a week. I //may—hope to return on the // 22nd—certainly not//later than Jan. 25th. Will//you plan to come on the 25th//or after—I will be staying// with Jean LeDoux if you//wish to reach me. Will write//you from N.Y. if I can—//Looking forward to your coming// through this poor door—G." Sent to Charles Wickham Moore.

Sent to Charles Wickham Moore as 1959 New Year's greeting. Handwritten by GOK in black ink on verso: "Just to remind you of//Abiquiu and greet you//for Xmas and 59//Sorry you do not come.//I can't promise anything as//funny as Alans Story but//it is good here as you know//G."

referred_to_by.value: Sent to Charles Wickham Moore in 1959. Handwritten by Georgia O'Keeffe in pencil on verso: "Thanks for the record—It is//lovely—I have another recording//of same but not nearly so good.//We had a fine Xmas eve—//very amusing—rain for Xmas//—snow since—I went to the//ranch this AM—had a fine//walk in the new snow with//the dogs—It was startingly//beautiful—//When will you be//coming? Have written Rolf//but have not heard from her.//Best to you—G."
